          <subparagraph>
            <num>B.</num>
            <content>
              <p>Annex B – Summary of SI provisions which come into force pre-exit</p>
            </content>
          </subparagraph>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph>
          <content>
            <p>As set out in section I (2), a small number of provisions in these SIs come into effect before 29 March 2019. These are provisions which allow the regulators to make the necessary preparations, but they are also specifically designed to prepare for a “no deal” scenario. The table below summarises these provisions. </p>
            <table uk:widths="2.85in 4.55in">
              <tr>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">SI</p>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">Pre-exit provisions</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">The Collective Investment Schemes (Amendment etc.) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019</p>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">Provisions relating to the T(M)PR for standalone EEA UCITS and sub-funds come into force before exit day. </p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text" />
                  <p class="ia-table-text">Provisions giving the FCA the power to open its notification window for alternative investment funds before exit day, providing time for those funds to notify their intent to enter the regime before exit day, and for the FCA to process the notifications.</p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text" />
                  <p class="ia-table-text">Minor and technical amendments to ensure cross-references to other legislation work effectively.</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">The Alternative Investment Fund Managers (Amendment etc.) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019</p>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">None</p>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>
